Some victims and families of those who died at the hands of apartheid police feel the Truth and Reconciliation Commission did not give them recourse and justice. One such victim is Carla Motau, South Africa's ruling African National Congress struggle veteran who lost her husband, Peter, in Swaziland.

He was killed in a 1986 Vlakplaas operation. She says while the man who led the operation sought forgiveness from her, there were others involved who weren't held accountable. Noma Bolani reports... --SABC--